#. <section class="sutta" id="sn17.35"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn17.35:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 17"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 17"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.35:0.2"
msgid "4. Catutthavagga"
msgstr "4. The Fourth Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 35. Acirapakkantasutta → attavadhasuttaṃ (bj) | pakkanta (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn17.35:0.3"
msgid "35. Acirapakkantasutta"
msgstr "35. Shortly After He Left"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.241"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.35:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate acirapakkante "
"devadatte."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak "
"Mountain, not long after Devadatta had left."

msgctxt "sn17.35:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā devadattaṃ ārabbha bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha spoke to the mendicants about Devadatta:"

msgctxt "sn17.35:1.3"
msgid ""
"“attavadhāya, bhikkhave, devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, "
"parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi."
msgstr ""
"“Possessions, honor, and popularity came to Devadatta for his own ruin and "
"downfall."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.35:2.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kadalī attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ "
"deti;"
msgstr "It’s like a banana tree …"

msgctxt "sn17.35:2.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, "
"parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.35:3.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, veḷu attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti;"
msgstr "or a bamboo …"

msgctxt "sn17.35:3.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, "
"parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.35:4.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, naḷo attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti;"
msgstr "or a reed, all of which bear fruit to their own ruin and downfall …"

msgctxt "sn17.35:4.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, "
"parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.35:5.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, assatarī attavadhāya gabbhaṃ gaṇhāti, parābhavāya "
"gabbhaṃ gaṇhāti;"
msgstr "It’s like a mule, which becomes pregnant to its own ruin and downfall."

msgctxt "sn17.35:5.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, "
"parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, possessions, honor, and popularity came to Devadatta for "
"his own ruin and downfall."

msgctxt "sn17.35:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko."
msgstr "So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”"

msgctxt "sn17.35:5.4"
msgid "Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr "That’s how you should train.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.35:6.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn17.35:6.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.35:7.1"
msgid "“Phalaṃ ve kadaliṃ hanti,"
msgstr "“The banana tree is destroyed by its own fruit,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn17.35:7.2"
msgid "phalaṃ veḷuṃ phalaṃ naḷaṃ;"
msgstr "as are the bamboo and the reed."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn17.35:7.3"
msgid "Sakkāro kāpurisaṃ hanti,"
msgstr "Honor destroys a sinner,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn17.35:7.4"
msgid "gabbho assatariṃ yathā”ti."
msgstr "as pregnancy destroys a mule.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn17.35:7.5"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
